<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a6192e1-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s6711"><num value="6711">§ 6711.</num><heading> Functional regulation of insurance</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The insurance activities of any person (including a national bank exercising its power to act as agent under <ref href="/us/usc/t12/s92">section 92 of title 12</ref>) shall be functionally regulated by the States, subject to <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s6701">section 6701 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7a6192e2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/106/102/tIII/s301">Pub. L. 106–102, title III, § 301</ref>, <date date="1999-11-12">Nov. 12, 1999</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/113/1407">113 Stat. 1407</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
